e newly conquered kingdom. In Britain the variants  <b>Allan</b>  and  <b>Allen</b>  are considerably less frequent, and generally represent transferred uses of surname forms, whereas in America all three forms of the name are approximately equally common.  See also  Alun ."]},{"name":"Albert","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Albert</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, displacing the Old English form <i>Æþelbeorht</i>. The name is popular in a variety of forms in Western Europe, and has been traditional in a number of European princely families. It was out of favour in England for centuries, however, and the revival of its popularity in the 19th century was largely in honour of  Queen Victoria's  consort,  Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Griffri \" Fychan\" ap Meurig was born about 1300, in Oswestry, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"ABT    1300–Deceased":"umbes 1300–Surnud","1347–Female":"1347–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1378–Male":"1378–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","ABT    1300":"umbes 1300","1347":"1347","1378":"1378","1300":"1300","of,Oswestry,Shropshire,England":"Oswestry, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT    1300–Deceased":"noin 1300–Kuollut","1347–Female":"1347–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1378–Male":"1378–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","ABT    1300":"noin 1300","1347":"1347","1378":"1378","1300":"1300","of,Oswestry,Shropshire,England":"Oswestry, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT    1300–Deceased":"environ 1300–Décédé","1347–Female":"1347–Décédée","–Female":"Décédée","1378–Male":"1378–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","ABT    1300":"environ 1300","1347":"1347","1378":"1378","1300":"1300","of,Oswestry,Shropshire,England":"Oswestry, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary"